imum cumulative GPA of 2.5 in prerequisite CHEM and BIOL courses listed in items 4-6 below.","[Page 1] 4. Completion of BIOL 180, BIOL 200 (minimum grade 2.3), AND BIOL 220.","[Page 1] 5. Completion of one of the following chemistry series:","[Page 1] a. CHEM 142, CHEM 152, CHEM 162","[Page 1] b. CHEM 143, CHEM 153","[Page 1] c. CHEM 145, CHEM 155, CHEM 165","[Page 1] 6. Completion of either CHEM 223, CHEM 237, or CHEM 335","[Page 1] Grade Requirements:","[Page 1] 1. All courses taken to fulfill requirements must be taken for a letter (numerical) grade unless the course is","[Page 1] offered credit/no credit.","[Page 1] 3. A minimum grade of 1.8 must be achieved in all required and elective courses (see below) for them to","[Page 1] be used toward degree requirements for graduation.","[Page 2] Supporting Requirements (in addition to the prerequisite Biology and Chemistry Courses listed above):","[Page 2] BIOCHEMISTRY - Choose One Option:","[Page 2] MATHEMATICS – Choose One Option:","[Page 2] 1. BIOC 405 (3), 406 (3)","[Page 2] 1. MATH 124 (5)","[Page 2] 2. BIOC 440 (4), 441 (4), 442 (4)","[Page 2] 2. MATH 134 (5)","[Page 2] 3. Q SCI 291 (5)","[Page 2] Please note that CHEM 224, 238, and 239 may be needed, Analysis for Biologists I","[Page 2] for students pursuing graduate work: MATH 124 (5), 125","[Page 2] (5), 126 (5) -OR- QSCI 291 (5), 292 (5), 381 (5)","[Page 2] STATISTICS – Choose One Option:","[Page 2] PHYSICS – Choose One Option:","[Page 2] 1. BIOST 310 (4)","[Page 2] 1. PHYS 114 (4), 115 (4)","[Page 2] 2. Q SCI 381 (5)","[Page 2] 2. PHYS 121 (5), 122 (5)","[Page 2] 3. STAT 220 (5)","[Page 2] 3. PHYS 141 (5), 142 (5)","[Page 2] 4. STAT 311 (5)","[Page 2] Freshman Year: Typically, students will complete Inorganic Chemistry and Math requirements along with other general","[Page 2] education requirements.","[Page 2] Sophomore Year: Students should complete the Introductory Biology and Organic Chemistry requirements and continue","[Page 2] requirements."],"parsedU